rComments: Best prof ever! Her lectures are amazing and enthusiastic. I love her presentations and she always makes it interesting and energetic. The French Community Project takes a lot of time on your own and there were a lot of written assignments that worth a lot. I would recommend it to French Immersion students with strong reading, writing and listening

Prof. Beauquis is inviting & enthusiastic when relaying course content. I'm not one for group assignments but she is encouraging to even the most soft-spoken in the class. She is reasonably understanding when it comes to needing extensions. She is open to arranging meetings outside of her office hours too which helps those of us working tricky hrs.

An AMAZING prof! Very kind and sincere - truly wants everyone to succeed! Her lectures are thorough but simplified so that the material is made easier to understand. 100% there to help you when you need it. I wouldn't say she's an easy marker but she is very fair - the grade you get is what you deserve! She's fun and has great enthusiasm! Love her!
AWESOME. Nice. Cute and really thorough. Why ask for another prof? She is the BEST!!!!

BEST teacher I ever had at university. Honestly, she makes learning so much fun and her enthusiasm really rubs off on you, making a 3 hour lecture bearable - to the point that even after class is over, you still want to continue! :)
Best French prof! I love her enthusiasm and she marks fairly and understands my writing unlike other French profs at UTSC. I'm really sad that she won't be teaching next year :(
enthusiastic french prof!! She made is extremely helpful and caring ^^

Beauquis is an absolutely amazing woman. She works very hard for the benefit of the students, and clearly loves her job. She is the most welcoming and sincerely caring professor you will ever have at UTSC.

Although she only taught me once, in 2008, she is by far the best I have ever had! She is VERY sweet, VERY caring, and VERY knowledgeable! She is always there to give out a hand, and is very considerate, whether she still taught me or not! Other professors, even in other fields, should learn a bit from her!
Wonderful prof and human being in general. Her door is wide open and she is extremely dedicated and a wonderful role model for the teachers of tomorrow.

best prof EVER ! her class might seem a little tough at first and it might seem like you're doing much more than the other classes, but you'll realize how much of an advantage you have during exams ! she'll help you and encourage you as much as she can, and makes sure everyone understands the material ! by far my favourite at utsc
The BEST. Period. She goes out of her way to help you, I honestly cannot say enough! She is just an genuinely great person and an awesome prof!
Teaches well. Very organized. Lots of homework and readings though!

extremely nice lady, very helpful but only prob is if you do not understand french u can become very scared of seeing her..she;s type to go out of her way to help u or say hello to u in the halls..n all u can do is say oui oui...but if she spoke english too she would be one of the best esp in terms of enthusiasm!
Very enthusiastic and nice. Explains the material really well and always there for you to help you out anytime
Excellent...highly recommend!

Luv her!!!! She's the best prof at UTSC and one of the best teachers I've ever had! She's willing to help and very approachable. I suggest going out of your way to get INTO her classes, you won't regret it!
shes very energentic and approachable.
not the easiest prof but very helpful
Awsome teacher, shes great, loves her job and loves to help her students to make sure they succeed. You can tell she works really hard. Merci madame, God bless you.
Corinne is the most energetic prof I have ever met. She is great!!!
Terrible.
great prof. she really knows what she's doing. and one can see she really loves teaching the subject.
She's a great prof. It's apparent she loves what she's doing. Great explanations.

Prof. Beauquis is very enthusiastic about what she teaches, and it rubs off on her students! She makes coming to class very enjoyable, offering students the chance to actively participate. Her lessons are both clear and interesting, and she goes out of her way to make sure everyone understands. Definately one of the best at UTSC! She's great!
